<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 3:20AM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...Light Rain and Snow Possible Along With Strong Winds...
Rain and snow will continue into tonight. Snow levels will push
above 5500 feet before dropping to valley floors with a cold
front. Expect 1 to 3 inches with locally higher amounts. With the
cold front, strong winds may produce near whiteout conditions and
a brief burst of heavier snow. Snow showers and gusty winds will
persist overnight.</description>
